==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uroglaucin
<hw>U`ro*glau"cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[1st
<ets>uro-</ets> + L. <ets>glaucus</ets> bright.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A body identical with indigo blue, occasionally found
in the urine in degeneration of the kidneys. It is readily formed by
oxidation or decomposition of indican.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Urohaematin</ent>⟦br⟧
